    <title>Rational pullbacks of toric foliations</title>
    <summary>  This article is dedicated to the study of foliations on a simplicial complete
toric variety $X$ and their pullbacks by dominant rational maps $\mathbb{P}^n
\dashrightarrow X$. First, we construct moduli spaces for singular foliations
on $X$ using the Cox coordinate ring. Then we show that the foliations induced
by the fibers of such maps define closed subvarieties of some logarithmic
irreducible components of the corresponding moduli space. In the case of
foliations of codimension 1, we characterize the singular and Kupka scheme of
foliations on a toric surface and their corresponding pullbacks. We also
describe their first order unfoldings and deformations.
</summary>
